<subSubSection id="CC1344167260355F0889DEFEA31F938F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7323CC4CE2C756D8511C261CA4EE4C11" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="972460C129722EFB2126809EE56F8ED7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The males of this species can be easily distinguished from all other members of the genus by the aedeagus and phallobase with one pair of processes; and the aedeagal shafts substantially shorter than the basal appendages.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
